131. Tunc licet a Pico] Picus was a son of Saturnus, and an early mythical king of Italy. ‘ Omnem Titanida pugnam ' is the Same as ‘omnes Titanas pugnatores! They were sons of Earth, and Prometheus was one of them. The force of 'ipsulm’ Prometheus himself, is that he was reputed to have been the creator of man. ‘Avus,' ‘proavus,' ‘abavus,’ ‘atavus,‘ ‘tritavus ' is the ascending scale, but each of these words is used generieally for ancestors. ‘Quo- cunque libro’ is any story book. Most MSS. have ‘tunc' or ‘tum' in v. 131, which is wanted after ‘si.’ Jahn [and Ribbeck] have ‘tu,' from P. and others. The Scholiast had ‘tu.’ [Ribbeck omits v. 134 from his text.]
